answers.answer: You may not have any this time. Every pregnancy is different. I hardly have any symptoms too but enough to know I'm pregnant. For instance the nose of a hound, constipation, headaches, zero patience...ha! I get waves of feeling like my stomach is going to turn but that is it.Enjoy!

I didnt start getting sickness until I hit 6 weeks with both of mine. Im now 18wks pregnant and still being sick badly, even on anti sickness meds. I wish it would stop. I hope you have a safe and enjoyable pregnancy.
I was like 8 or 9 weeks when a started feeling sick, but i didnt get it that bad it for very long and had no morning sickness at all with my first
I'm feeling the same. I'm 5 weeks and I am not feeling a whole lot. With my first two I was in horrible shape.

I havent had any of that lol! Today i feel really tired and i get cramps and if i sneeze or move too fast feels like ive pulled a muscle in my belly. Your not far ahead of me :) Hope you have a good and healthy pregnancy xxx
Sorry that was a reply to spiket77 but i wish all you ladies luck with the rest of your pregnancys x
Thanks! I get the pulling sensation if I laugh when lying down or sneeze. The fatigue is a major sign. You are just fine. Good luck to you too!

I found out at 5 weeks and 3 days ironically. I am now 35 weeks and 3 days. Wowww exactly 30 weeks ago lol. I never had one day of morning sickness, maybeeee 5 times of the nausea. Feeling...headaches, and verrrry tired and my breasts were tender. Im very thankful had no sickness, I heard if u don't get it big chance of a boy... well im having a boy :-) congrats and goood luck mamas
Thats interesting. Because my other children are girls. Maybe this is a boy. Lol
I had loads of sickness with my first all the way through and that was a boy im hoping for another boy but aslong as its healthy either way im happy :)

I started getting sickness at 7wks and still have it if I stop my medicine im 23wks1d now this is my second and I'm having a little girl my first pregnancy I didn't get any morning sickness till 11wks and it hit hard and heavy I was on a medicated pump so I could even eat...my first was a little boy

I never had morning sickness. My mom was shocked but thats how I knew I was having a girl is she didnt have morning sickness either with any of her pregnancies and had 3 girls. My sisters had 5 boys between the 2 of them and had morning sickness with all :) I know thats my silly theory but it proved true because I am due with my first little girl in less than 4 weeks!! YEAH!! But I would just say consider yourself lucky to not have it or not have it yet. I dont even have heartburn either which my mom thinks is crazy amazing. I guess my little girl will be bald lol
I had no sickness with any of my pregnancies...just turned 19 weeks and so hoping it doesn't come back to bite me at the end of the pregnancy lol

With my first son, I started getting sick a week before I found out. I ended up being diagnosed with hyperemesis at 6 Weeks and gestational diabetes at 15 Weeks. This pregnancy, sickness started around 6 Weeks, but wasn't no where near as severe with my son. Even my diabetes test at 14 weeks came back better than me not being pregnant. I had an 80% chance of getting hyperemesis again, and it didn't. Every pregnancy is different so don't fret too much! Enjoy not being sick in case it sets in in a few Weeks! Good luck!

U might be having a different gender this time and have different sypmtoms this time. I hardly had any symptoms in my first trimester. Only slight nausea if i got hungry and tiredness but this didnt start until about 6 weeks.
When you all first felt sick was you confussed whether it was the morning sickness starting or hunger?
It honestly didnt kick in till the day after I took the test bout 15 weeks
